**Project Name:** EduTrack Lite

**Problem:** Many schools still manage student results manually, leading to grading errors, poor record keeping, and limited performance tracking.

**Users:** Secondary schools, tutors, and school administrators.

**Build:** EduTrack Lite is a lightweight student result dashboard built with HTML, CSS, JavaScript, Local Storage, and Chart.js. It supports result entry, automatic grading, performance analytics, and printable report cards.

**Impact:** It improves accuracy, saves time, and helps educators visualize student performance.

**Scalability:** Future improvements include backend integration, multi-student database support, authentication, and cloud storage.

**AI Disclosure:** AI-assisted tools were used for debugging guidance and code refinement during development.

Excited to submit my project **EduTrack Lite** for the NextGen Knowledge Showcase.

EduTrack Lite is a lightweight student performance management system designed to simplify result tracking, improve grading accuracy, and provide performance insights through visual analytics.

Built with HTML, CSS, JavaScript, Local Storage, and Chart.js.

